1
00:00:00,720 --> 00:00:01,726
They brought us in through the door

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:05,417
They brought us in, they detained me on the charge of neglecting prayer

3
00:00:06,104 --> 00:00:08,267
I told them, I did not neglect prayer

4
00:00:08,348 --> 00:00:09,827
I did not neglect it, I have a dispensation

5
00:00:10,274 --> 00:00:12,604
They answered, No, you neglected prayer, give us your name

6
00:00:12,958 --> 00:00:15,024
I gave them my full name, and my mother's name

7
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:19,107
And I took out the phone, and while searching me they found the cigarettes

8
00:00:19,950 --> 00:00:22,139
In the <i>izar</i>, and they went crazy

9
00:00:23,225 --> 00:00:24,849
Interviewer: What do you mean by <i>izar</i>?

10
00:00:26,815 --> 00:00:30,121
These pants were not allowed to be worn like this

11
00:00:30,497 --> 00:00:33,204
Unless they had an <i>izar</i> [wrapper] tight at the bottom

12
00:00:35,011 --> 00:00:39,367
Only a short <i>izar</i> like this—there was no long <i>izar</i>

13
00:00:40,293 --> 00:00:43,350
Interviewer: Did you put the cigarettes inside the waistband of the pants?

14
00:00:43,410 --> 00:00:46,821
There was elastic at the bottom of the pants, I put them in there

15
00:00:47,399 --> 00:00:49,582
And as you know, wide pants do not show anything

16
00:00:50,421 --> 00:00:51,423
And when they searched me, they found them

17
00:00:52,654 --> 00:00:54,169
Here, at the bottom of the pants

18
00:00:54,636 --> 00:00:58,336
Interviewer: Describe how you stashed the cigarettes. Where did you put them?

19
00:01:04,029 --> 00:01:05,029
This is the cigarette pack

20
00:01:05,532 --> 00:01:07,166
Let me toss it here

21
00:01:07,910 --> 00:01:09,374
Interviewer: Were the pants wide?

22
00:01:09,407 --> 00:01:11,094
Yes, the pants were wide and the cigarette pack dropped to the bottom

23
00:01:14,001 --> 00:01:15,601
And here it is wide, and at the bottom it is tight, it does not show

24
00:01:15,626 --> 00:01:16,659
Because it is wide, nothing shows in it?

25
00:01:16,706 --> 00:01:19,147
Yes, because the pants are long and wide, it bunches up

26
00:01:20,738 --> 00:01:21,757
It does not show at all

27
00:01:21,805 --> 00:01:23,644
Interviewer: How many packs of cigarettes were you carrying?

28
00:01:23,731 --> 00:01:26,117
I was carrying two packs, one for me and the other for my brother

29
00:01:26,337 --> 00:01:27,354
My brother went to prayer

30
00:01:27,943 --> 00:01:29,035
And he left his cigarettes with me

31
00:01:29,510 --> 00:01:30,570
Were the two packs full?

32
00:01:30,687 --> 00:01:33,544
No, each one had about seven or eight cigarettes

33
00:01:34,653 --> 00:01:35,653
They went crazy

34
00:01:36,064 --> 00:01:37,377
Interviewer: And after they found the cigarettes?

35
00:01:39,510 --> 00:01:41,078
At first they took my name

36
00:01:41,672 --> 00:01:43,576
Interviewer: Where did they take your name?
Witness: They stopped us here

37
00:01:44,532 --> 00:01:48,236
There was a man sitting, bearded

38
00:01:49,622 --> 00:01:50,765
What is your name?

39
00:01:51,753 --> 00:01:52,873
He wrote it in the notebook

40
00:01:53,624 --> 00:01:55,849
And your mother's name, your birth date, and your charge

41
00:01:56,849 --> 00:01:58,649
He wrote, Neglecting prayer, I told him, I am not negligent

42
00:01:58,713 --> 00:02:00,232
He said, Be quiet, you neglected prayer

43
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:03,694
And he wrote for those who came with me

44
00:02:04,848 --> 00:02:06,660
He turned his face and then went to that church

45
00:02:08,260 --> 00:02:10,967
The main church, or I do not know what they call it

46
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:14,586
On the computer he recorded our names

47
00:02:15,497 --> 00:02:18,460
He said, Go inside now

48
00:02:19,181 --> 00:02:23,805
Interviewer: The person who recorded your name and took your address and information about you?

49
00:02:24,276 --> 00:02:27,158
Interviewer: Was there a desk or a table here?
Witness: Yes, there was a table

50
00:02:27,191 --> 00:02:29,878
Interviewer: How many chairs were there?
Witness: A table and chairs

51
00:02:30,216 --> 00:02:33,011
It was a guesthouse, like it belonged to their father

52
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:36,612
There was a table and sofa sets

53
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,033
Interviewer: By the <i>diwan</i> [administrative hall], do you mean chairs?

54
00:02:39,091 --> 00:02:40,868
Yes, chairs, and they sat on them

55
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:41,920
Where exactly were they sitting?

56
00:02:42,075 --> 00:02:45,688
Here was a sitting area, and inside it went lengthwise

57
00:02:45,850 --> 00:02:47,394
Because the table was in this direction

58
00:02:47,838 --> 00:02:49,438
And the other was lengthwise, and the other table was here

59
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:51,959
They were sitting, relaxed

60
00:02:51,995 --> 00:02:53,792
Interviewer: How many people sat here, or was it just one person?

61
00:02:53,853 --> 00:02:55,266
One person was the one who took the information

62
00:02:55,373 --> 00:02:58,476
But as for soldiers, as they say

63
00:02:58,894 --> 00:02:59,920
This room was packed

64
00:03:00,514 --> 00:03:02,868
On the roof, at the door, or somewhere else

65
00:03:03,575 --> 00:03:04,947
They were spread out around this place

66
00:03:05,288 --> 00:03:07,601
Interviewer: After he took your name and information exactly

67
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:12,464
Was it the same person who took you to the detention room, the cell?

68
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,970
Or did he assign someone else, meaning another ISIS member?

69
00:03:15,027 --> 00:03:17,524
No, he said, Go straight into the hall

70
00:03:17,688 --> 00:03:18,968
Interviewer: Without anyone accompanying you?

71
00:03:19,016 --> 00:03:21,873
Yes, you can't move around here

72
00:03:22,403 --> 00:03:23,408
You can't do anything

73
00:03:23,576 --> 00:03:25,719
Because they are all present, you can't do anything or run away

74
00:03:25,779 --> 00:03:29,360
The place was closed. They shut the door on us right after we went in

75
00:03:29,454 --> 00:03:33,810
Interviewer: During this period, from your entry
through the door until you reached this place

76
00:03:34,496 --> 00:03:40,483
Exactly, did they tie your hands with a piece of cloth, or with cuffs?

77
00:03:40,724 --> 00:03:41,901
Or were your hands free?

78
00:03:42,007 --> 00:03:43,823
No, my hands were free

79
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:46,782
As I told you, when they heard that I was neglecting prayer

80
00:03:47,316 --> 00:03:50,019
They pushed me, and then they found the cigarettes

81
00:03:51,286 --> 00:03:54,715
They pushed us and took us into the hall

82
00:03:54,788 --> 00:03:56,194
Interviewer: The first time you came to this place

83
00:03:56,421 --> 00:03:59,761
Did you imagine this place was a prison, or were you surprised that it was a prison?

84
00:03:59,854 --> 00:04:00,882
It didn't cross my mind that it was a prison

85
00:04:01,262 --> 00:04:04,117
Interviewer: So it was a surprise for you?
Witness: Yes

86
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:06,069
I thought it was normal

87
00:04:06,563 --> 00:04:09,167
Ten minutes or a quarter hour, then they would say, Go

88
00:04:09,425 --> 00:04:12,097
Interviewer: Not the duration of prison
time, but when you first came to this place?

89
00:04:12,157 --> 00:04:13,536
No, I didn't know there was a prison here

90
00:04:13,868 --> 00:04:14,891
I absolutely didn't know

91
00:04:15,164 --> 00:04:17,404
I was surprised to find people imprisoned here

92
00:04:18,891 --> 00:04:21,228
Interviewer: In this place, when you first came in here

93
00:04:21,328 --> 00:04:23,948
And as you entered through the main door

94
00:04:24,342 --> 00:04:27,960
And the ISIS member took your information

95
00:04:28,073 --> 00:04:29,760
Until they took you into the hall

96
00:04:30,498 --> 00:04:32,049
That period, about how long did it take?

97
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:35,722
Minutes, or half an hour, or an hour—more than that or less?

98
00:04:35,895 --> 00:04:36,895
No, no

99
00:04:38,474 --> 00:04:41,328
I told you we were three people, it took about

100
00:04:41,915 --> 00:04:47,130
Half an hour—he took our information and our belongings, then to the hall

101
00:04:47,432 --> 00:04:49,204
Interviewer: In this half hour or less?

102
00:04:49,438 --> 00:04:52,950
From when they brought you in through the main gate
to this person, then you entered the hall

103
00:04:53,728 --> 00:04:57,226
Did you hear people screaming?

104
00:04:57,353 --> 00:04:59,486
Or did you hear people being tortured?

105
00:04:59,721 --> 00:05:02,927
Did you hear loud sounds or strange sounds?

106
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:07,033
Did you hear women’s voices, for example?

107
00:05:07,225 --> 00:05:10,545
And was this prison for women? Had you heard that? Or do you not know?

108
00:05:10,805 --> 00:05:12,280
No, I didn’t hear, and I don’t know

109
00:05:12,648 --> 00:05:15,200
But I could hear them talking inside

110
00:05:15,450 --> 00:05:19,030
Those outside were shouting, Be quiet, everyone, no one speak

111
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,207
From here

112
00:05:21,434 --> 00:05:23,612
When we came, there was a group before us

113
00:05:24,249 --> 00:05:28,279
They brought them into the hall, and had not yet taken them out to the prison

114
00:05:28,847 --> 00:05:31,213
Interviewer: Didn’t you hear the sounds of people they were torturing?
Witness: No

115
00:05:31,287 --> 00:05:33,408
Interviewer: Before you entered the prison

116
00:05:33,722 --> 00:05:35,605
From when you entered through the main gate up to this room

117
00:05:35,665 --> 00:05:37,498
Until they took you into the prison?
Witness: No

118
00:05:37,794 --> 00:05:39,966
I didn’t hear, but in that church

119
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,100
I have a cousin who went in there

120
00:05:42,690 --> 00:05:44,557
The torture there is not normal, he said
